HEADWORD: Undergown
<hw>Un"der*gown`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A gown worn under
another, or under some other article of dress.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>An <qex>undergown</qex> and kirtle of pale sea-green silk.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir W. Scott.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

